## Design Patterns

### 1. Container/Presentational Pattern

```typescript
// Container (Smart) - Index.tsx
export default function Index() {
  const [selectedSection, setSelectedSection] = useState(null);

  return (
    <HeroSection {...profileData} />
    <Timeline items={timeline} />
  );
}

// Presentational (Dumb) - HeroSection.tsx
export const HeroSection = ({ name, title, bio, skills }) => {
  return (
    <section>
      <h1>{name}</h1>
      <p>{bio}</p>
      {/* ... */}
    </section>
  );
};
```

**Pattern:** Index.tsx (smart) passes data to components (dumb)

### 2. Composition Pattern

Components built from smaller UI primitives:

```typescript
<Card>
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <Badge>{status}</Badge>
    <h3>{title}</h3>
  </div>
  <p>{description}</p>
</Card>
```

### 3. Props Configuration Pattern

All customization through props:

```typescript
// Instead of hardcoding, accept props
interface TimelineProps {
  items: TimelineItem[];
}

export const Timeline = ({ items }: TimelineProps) => {
  // Render items dynamically
};
```

### 4. Single Source of Truth (SSOT)

All data centralized in one file:

```typescript
// src/data/portfolioData.ts is THE source
// Don't duplicate data in components
// Don't hardcode content
// All mutations happen in one place
```

### 5. Layered Architecture

```
Presentation Layer (Components)
    â–¼
Logic Layer (Hooks, Utils)
    â–¼
Data Layer (portfolioData.ts)
    â–¼
Styling Layer (CSS, Tailwind)
```

