## Code Conventions

### TypeScript

**Strict mode enabled** - all code must be type-safe.

```typescript
// âœ“ Good - typed
interface UserProps {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}

const User = ({ name, age }: UserProps) => {
  return <div>{name} - {age}</div>;
};

// âœ— Bad - not typed
const User = (props) => {
  return <div>{props.name}</div>;
};
```

### Naming Conventions

#### Files

```
Components:           PascalCase
  âœ“ HeroSection.tsx
  âœ“ SkillsEvolutionRadar.tsx

Utilities:           camelCase
  âœ“ use-mobile.tsx
  âœ“ utils.ts

Data files:          camelCase
  âœ“ portfolioData.ts
```

#### Variables & Functions

```typescript
// âœ“ Good
const profileData = {...};
const getSkillRating = (skill) => {...};
const handleClick = () => {...};
const isVisible = true;

// âœ— Bad
const PROFILEDATA = {...};       // All caps
const Profile_Data = {...};      // Snake case
const getskillrating = () => {}; // Missing camelCase
```

#### React Components

```typescript
// âœ“ Good - PascalCase, self-closing if no children
<HeroSection />
<Card className="p-4">
  Content
</Card>

// âœ— Bad - lowercase
<heroSection />
<card>Content</card>
```

#### CSS Classes

```typescript
// âœ“ Good - Tailwind utilities
className="flex items-center gap-4 p-6 bg-primary text-primary-foreground rounded-lg"

// âœ— Bad - custom classes (use Tailwind instead)
className="my-custom-class"
className="button--primary"
```

### Imports

**Organize imports in this order:**

```typescript
// 1. React & third-party libraries
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useRouter } from "react-router-dom";

// 2. Components (relative imports with @/ alias)
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { HeroSection } from "@/components/HeroSection";

// 3. Data/Utils
