```

**Always use path aliases:**

```typescript
// âœ“ Good - clear and consistent
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { profileData } from "@/data/portfolioData";

// âœ— Bad - relative paths are hard to read
import { Button } from "../../../components/ui/button";
import { profileData } from "../../data/portfolioData";
```

### Comments

Use comments for **why**, not **what**:

```typescript
// âœ“ Good - explains intent
// Fetch skills data for current year visualization
const currentYearSkills = skills.filter(s => s["2025"] > 0);

// âœ— Bad - just repeats code
// Filter skills where 2025 rating is greater than 0
